input_str: Today, in the biggest shake up of domestic Esports development, sees British Esports Association fully launch their website and project with more information on who is behind the project. Many of us who have been around for many many years in the Esports industry in the United Kingdom, will remember similar projects coming and going (UKeSA!!). However, back in July, British Esports Association announced itself to the UK. No-one really knew what they were setting out to do, what they wanted to achieve and what exactly they were going to do tackling any kind of issues
